      <div class="container  px-4 py-5" id="FAQ">
        <h2 class="mb-5">FAQ</h2>
        <div class="item border rounded p-3 shadow-sm bg-light mb-3">
            <p class="question fw-bold text-primary mb-1">1. How do I get a library card?</p>
            <span class="text-muted">To get a library card, simply visit the front desk with a valid ID and proof of address. Some libraries also allow online registration. Once issued, your card grants access to book borrowing, digital resources, and other library services.</span>
        </div>

        <div class="item border rounded p-3 shadow-sm bg-light mb-3">
            <p class="question fw-bold text-primary mb-1">2. How long can I borrow books, and can I renew them?</p>
            <span class="text-muted">Most books can be borrowed for 2-4 weeks, depending on library policies. If you need more time, you can renew your books online, through the library app, or by visiting in person—unless the book is on hold for another reader.</span>
        </div>

        <div class="item border rounded p-3 shadow-sm bg-light mb-3">
            <p class="question fw-bold text-primary mb-1">3. Does the library offer digital resources like e-books or audiobooks?</p>
            <span class="text-muted">Yes! Many libraries provide access to e-books, audiobooks, online journals, and research databases. You can access these resources through the library’s website or app using your library card.</span>
        </div>

        <div class="item border rounded p-3 shadow-sm bg-light mb-3">
            <p class="question fw-bold text-primary mb-1">4. Are there quiet study areas or meeting rooms available?</p>
            <span class="text-muted">Yes, most libraries have dedicated quiet zones for studying and private meeting rooms for group work. Some meeting rooms may require reservations, which can be made online or at the library’s front desk.</span>
        </div>

        <div class="item border rounded p-3 shadow-sm bg-light ">
            <p class="question fw-bold text-primary mb-1">5. What happens if I return a book late?</p>
            <span class="text-muted">Late returns may result in a small overdue fee, depending on the library's policy. Some libraries have eliminated late fees, but if you lose a book, you may need to replace it or pay a fine. Always check due dates to avoid penalties!</span>
        </div>
    </div>


